Quickstrike:








Quickstrike studied Transulas carefully. "Ain't that somethin'," he said, 
somewhat amazed by the physic ablity the spider had. He looked back at his 
now braced left foreclaw. It looked a little strange, but at least there was 
less pain when he scurried around. He wouldn't bang it into things and 
accidenily let it droop it down to the ground. It was a rather nasty wound. 
It was a one and a half long gash to the outter side of his claw, on the 
area that once was his upper leg.

"Where are we's goin'?" he asked again, getting a little impatient.
